derivation: a primitive root (perhaps rather the same as H4184 (מוּשׁ) through the idea of receding by contact);
outline:
1. to depart, remove
    1. (Qal)
      1. to depart
      2. to remove
      3. to be removed (of inanimate objects)
    2. (Hiphil) to remove, depart
kjv_def: cease, depart, go back, remove, take away.
strongs_def: to withdraw (both literally and figuratively, whether intransitive or transitive)
